  "correctAnswer": "A",
  "explanation": "To find $f(x + 3)$, substitute $(x + 3)$ for $x$ in the original function:\n\n$f(x + 3) = 2(x + 3)^2 - 8(x + 3) + 6$\n\nExpand $(x + 3)^2$:\n$(x + 3)^2 = x^2 + 6x + 9$\n\nSubstitute:\n$f(x + 3) = 2(x^2 + 6x + 9) - 8(x + 3) + 6$\n$= 2x^2 + 12x + 18 - 8x - 24 + 6$\n$= 2x^2 + 12x - 8x + 18 - 24 + 6$\n$= 2x^2 + 4x + 0$\n$= 2x^2 + 4x$\n\nTherefore, $f(x + 3) = 2x^2 + 4x$.",
